Police in Anambra State have arrested a 46-year-old man, Michael Nwoha for allegedly having carnal knowledge of three underaged boys. Anambra State Police Command’s spokesperson, SP Haruna Mohammed said the arrest was effected on Saturday, after a tip off. He said, “On the 2/10/2020 at about 8:30pm, following a tip off, Police detectives attached to 3-3 Division arrested one Michael Nwoha ‘m’ aged 46years native of Uzuakoli in Bende LGA of Abia State, but resides at No.10 Uke Street 3-3 Nkwelle Ezunaka in Oyi LGA of Anambra State. “Suspect allegedly had carnal knowledge against the order of nature with three Small boys of six, 14 and 17years on different occasions. “Suspect has equally made a voluntary confessional statement to the police and blamed his act on demons.” Haruna said police officers visited the scene of the crime and the three victims involved were taken to the hospital for medical examination. He added that the Commissioner of Police, CP John B. Abang has ordered for immediate transfer of the case to the State Criminal investigation Department (CID)for discreet investigation after which the suspect would be brought to book.